<Author>chrysemis
<Content>rough around the edges This hotel has the potential to be a nice extended stay hotel, but it currently has things to be desired. As also previously stated, the hotel was completing renovations during my stay (I was told that the first floor was the last to be worked on). As such, the rooms were nice (granite counters, full size fridge, comfortable bed, 2 flat screen TVs), but paint/glue fumes were noticeable in the hallways and rooms. Also, other coworkers and I noticed things that still needed attention in our hotel rooms -- bathroom vent cover missing, noisy ceiling fan, water leak from the ceiling, light fixture not working. Two out of the 5 large exercise equipments in the fitness room also were out of order.The evening reception was nice. Wine and beverages, salad, and hot snacks are available in a serve yourself set-up. The manager even occasionally went around to greet guests and offer to take away used plates and glasses. The breakfast selections, however, while hot, were generally of defrost-heat-n-serve quality. The waffle maker was a hit, but disappointing items included the completely albino hashbrowns and doughy breakfast burritos.Overall, this hotel could be better than it's currently being managed. 
