<Author>DenverWriter
<Content>Okay Stay, but beware We stayed for six nights. It's a good property with convenient access to all points in the Valley. Many restaurants nearby, including a Sweet Tomatoes, Lone Star Steakhouse, Fajitas and Outback all within walking distance. Nice park across the street to run. The rate we had was great ($109/night). Now for the not so good. They are doing extensive remodelling so there is a good deal of noise (drilling, hammering, etc.) during the day. Because of this activity, we had continuing visits from water bugs coming through the drains, one in particular was at least four inches long. After killing the invader, I took it to the front desk and the night manager did not offer anything other than It's Arizona...We've got bugs. Needless to say, I made sure that when we went to bed, we stuffed the drains with small hand towels so that we could sleep in peace. Other problems: The outer door card readers hardly ever worked, so you'd end up walking all the way around to the lobby entrance just to get in. The sprinklers burst one night, flooding the patio area and the breakfast left much to be desired. However, once the remodelling is finished, it'd be a great place for the price. 
