<Author>watermflower
<Content>Disappointed! I have stayed in two other cities: in a Homewood Suite hotel, and I loved those! We arrived at 9pm, at this Phoenix Homewood Suite, due to flight delays. There was one bed left. It was a room close to highway traffic.We walked into the room. It was supposed to be a suite, it was a 15x15 box, with a wall down the middle to make it a suite. The fire alarm was torn off the wall. The artificial plants had at least 4 years of dust on them. The ethernet would not work. The phone cord fell out of the wall, when we tried to put the phone near where we were sitting. The computer tech called once, we got disconnected...and although we called the front desk at least 3 more times about this connection problem: the computer tech never returned our calls.The bedding and kitchen were clean (except for the plants), but every door in the suite: hit a dresser or a table. The decor was very outdated and dark. (not like the pictures on the website). The halls were dark and somewhat spookey. We stayed 1 night (we were booked for 3), and we left for a better Hilton hotel in another part of the city.We were very disappointed! I will be much more reluctant to book Homewood Suites from now on. Don't assume that the pictures on the internet are what you will get! 
