<Author>AbCam
<Content>Good value for the money BUT...... This was our second time staying at this hotel, a week each time. The staff at this hotel is consistently great. Very friendly, polite, and anxious to please. The rooms could do with some updating. Our couch was very dirty and had stains. More light in the vanity area would be good. The bed is great. Our air conditioning quit working our 3rd day and it took until 7 pm to get someone up to fix it. They said we had froze it because we set the temp at 70 degrees - it was 99 outside and our room got the full blast of the sun. The free breakfast and manager's reception have gone downhill since last year. Every morning was the round re-heated eggs and sausage, one time cold french toast was in a basket on the side of the toaster ( but the toaster was broken on one side), bread and bagels, cereal, plus canned fruit cocktail. No yogurt this time, no variety. They ran out of styro cups and napkins. Last year the breakfast varied with bacon, pancakes, french toast in the steamer some days. The evening reception was hot dogs and canned baked beans once, canned ravioli once, mac and cheese next time. Last year was chicken wings, taco salad, etc. They did have lettuce, peppers, and broccoli out for salad bar each night. The beer dispenser was broken every day while we were there but wine was available, as were bottled sodas. The biggest complaint we have - and why we will not go back - is because of the noise of the air conditioner. It's a wall unit from floor to ceiling in the bedroom and is so loud it makes it difficult to sleep. We really like the hotel for the value and convenience but just can't over-come this noise at night. However, we would still recommend this hotel for families and anyone who is going to be in the area for an extended time that doesn't have a problem with the air conditioning noise. The kitchen is a big plus and there is a Fry's Market very close. The location is great for baseball spring training parks. 
