<Content>OK place, not as nice as other Homewood Suites This is the fourth different Homewood Suites I have stayed at, but unfortunately, is the first one to be somewhat disappointing. While it is still a good hotel with the amenities to make a business trip go smoothly, it lacks the attention to details in other Homewood suites I have accustomed to. Breakfast was weak with little variation. My room was showing its age, with stains in the tub and tired furniture. It was also facing I-17, so noise was a factor. I can also see that some of the rooms are very close (within several feet) of a giant billboard that is lit up at night.On the good side, the staff is friendly and helpful. There are several machines in the fitness room that actually work.Overall, it is OK for the value. If possible, ask for rooms that face the inside (not the freeway or Peoria Ave side). 
