<Author>Alamotraveler
<Content>Great Home Away From Home My family stayed her for over a week for the Junior Olympics baseball tournament. We were very pleased with the accommodations, which consisted of a large bedroom with king bed, TV, iron and ironing board, and 2 closets; a large bathroom; and a living area with sofa sleeper, recliner, TV, VCR, and fully-equipped kitchen with electric burners, microwave, dishwasher, coffeemaker, full-size fridge, and breakfast bar. The entire suite was very clean and comfortable. The A/C was making a loud noise when we arrived, but they promptly took care of it. Breakfast was very good and varied by the day, including cheese omelettes, egg disks, bacon, sausage, waffles, fruit, muffins, etc. Most surprising was the Manager's Reception from 5-7 p.m. Mon-Thurs., which really consisted of a full meal plus sodas, wine, and beer. Day 1 featured hot wings, BBQ sandwiches and a large salad bar. Day 2 featured turkey tetrazzini, salisbury steaks, and salad bar; Day 3 featured mac-n-cheese, a macaroni and ground beef casserole, and salad bar; and Day 4 featured high-quality hot dogs, potato salad, macaroni salad, etc. The reception meals, while not gourmet, were pretty good and saved our family a bundle. 
