<Author>mtnrealtor
<Content>Short Stay, Family of 5 We stayed Feb. 17 - Feb. 20, our family of 5 (kids 1, 5,  7) and my sister's family of 3 (one 5-yr. old). The rooms were great for us. Loved having full kitchen and sofa bed. Her room was on the highway side and was much bigger; ours was on the pool/sport court side. There was some noise from outside, but never too late and was always drowned out by the a/c.I was really impressed by the noise abatement between rooms. We were next door to a group of 4 teenage boys (there for a soccer tourney) and we never heard them except in the hallway.Breakfast was served every day and was mediocre at best, but good enough for us: cereal, bagels or danish, egg frisbees (warmed from frozen, I guess!), yogurt, toast (even had little pots of p'nut butter). We didn't stay for the dinners, but the one my sister had was disappointing - hot dogs and hamburgers on barbeque night. Oh, well - we didn't stay for the food.The staff was very pleasant and totally accomodating. We had requested a crib that was not in our room when we checked in - I called and it arrived right away. HOusekeeping came each day unless your privacy card was on the door. After 2 days w/the card out, they stuck a note under the door just to check in on us!The pool was adequate in size, but very poorly maintained. On our second day, they closed it to shock it, but the next day the water was so cloudy you couldn't see the second step. Don't know what was happening - again, we didn't stay for the pool, so didn't really affect us.The location was very close to lots of good restaurants, shopping and Castles 'n Coasters (small amusement park). Also across from a very large outdoor sports complex which had a HUGE open dog park, play structure, soccer/ball fields.In all, our stay was better than expected. I think I have learned not to expect much, though, so might be a little disappointing to the well-traveled! 
