<Content>I thought it was another Embassy Suites, but... Looking for prices and a free breakfast, I saw the Homewood Suites and read in other review sites that there was a free breakfast here. I got a Internet special price and called because I was in late (11pm). Checkin was fine and the staff attentive at that time. The premises was clean and a newer facility. The suite was fine with a kitchen, fridge pots and plates and two seat nook area. The room was large with a very quiet ceiling fan. The AC was loud. The breakfast was a fraud. I called and specifically asked if they had bacon, eggs and potatoes. The person said they have eggs and sausage, but no potatoes. Well, it was a continential breakfast with some steam tray of precooked scrambled egg patties and sausage. There was the other juices, bagels and breads, but the hot foods was out of a steam tray. I had breakfast the next day at a breakfast spot the next morning. Overall, nice spot except for the fraud breakfast. 
